# LCVB distractor pool — licensing

The 94 conversational `*.json` files in this directory are the
distractor pool used by the LCVB benchmark to produce
`canon_unified` prompts. They are **not** original LCVB content; they
are curated transformations of pre-existing publicly-available
conversational chat data.

## Two distinct rights apply

1. **Source data.** The underlying conversation text is from public
   conversational datasets. Whatever per-source licensing terms applied
   to those original conversations continue to apply to the text inside
   each `*.json` file. Inclusion of those conversations in this pool
   does not modify, override, or relicense the source data. If you
   intend to redistribute or commercially use the underlying chat
   content, consult the original source's license terms.

2. **LCVB curation.** The work performed on top of the source data —
   selection, deduplication, contamination filtering against the
   benchmark's evidence seeds, JSON normalization, and pool indexing —
   is the project's own contribution. That curation layer is released
   under **CC-BY-4.0**. Attribution should reference this repository.

## Provenance

`index.json` is the canonical inventory of pool entries. `provenance.tsv`
records which distractor groups were assigned to each scenario. Neither
file claims to identify the original publishing source of any
particular conversation; that lookup, if needed, is downstream of LCVB.

## No warranty

This pool is provided as-is for evaluation research. The LCVB project
makes no representation about the suitability of any individual
conversation in the pool for any purpose other than serving as
distractor context in this benchmark.
